tabularWorkflow.description:
This workflow will take Service Level Class(SLC) finds associated Storage Service Level Class(SSLC) and Protection Service Level Class (PSLC) or specific SSLC and PSLC and takes care of volume provisioning.
Workflow will understand the PSLC topology and prepares entire protection setup for volume as per given topology.
tabularWorkflow.name: Service based volume provisoning

workflow-command.commandAlias: Search data SVM in primary volumes storage node
Update Primary Volume details in Service Map table
Update Destination Volume to Service Mapping
Add rule for days of month snapshots
Add rule for days of week snapshots

user-input.description: Enables volume provision by selecting Service Level Class. Disabling this input provides manual selection of Storage Service Level Class and Protection Service Level Class
user-input.name: $UsingSLC

user-input.description: Selecting Service Class for provisioing. Second and Third column provides corresponding SSLC and PSLC attached with SLC.
user-input.name: $SLCName

user-input-type.query: SELECT DISTINCT service_level_name AS 'Service Level Class', storage_service_name AS 'Storage Service Level class', protection_service_name AS 'Protection Service Level class', comment AS 'Comment' FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT playground.service_level_class.service_level_name, playground.service_level_class.storage_service_name, playground.service_level_class.protection_service_name, playground.service_level_class.comment FROM playground.service_level_class, playground.storage_service_level, playground.protection_service_level, playground.aggregate_service_map WHERE playground.service_level_class.storage_service_name = playground.storage_service_level.storage_service_name AND playground.service_level_class.protection_service_name = playground.protection_service_level.protection_service_name AND playground.storage_service_level.storage_service_name = playground.aggregate_service_map.storage_service_name) AS sl WHERE '${UsingSLC}' = 'true'

user-input.description: Select SSLC against which volume needs to be provisioned
user-input.name: $SSLName

user-input-type.query: SELECT DISTINCT storage_service_name AS 'Name', iops_throttle AS 'IOPS Throttle(IOPS/TB)', MinimimSLA AS 'Minimim SLA(IOPS/TB)', comment AS 'Comment' FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT playground.storage_service_level.storage_service_name, playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle AS 'iops_throttle', IF (playground.storage_service_level.thin_min is NULL, CAST( playground.qos_default_values.thin_min * playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle / 100 AS SIGNED), CAST(playground.storage_service_level.thin_min * playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle / 100 AS SIGNED)) AS 'MinimimSLA', playground.storage_service_level.comment FROM playground.storage_service_level, playground.aggregate_service_map, playground.qos_default_values WHERE playground.storage_service_level.aggr_regex_enabled = 'false' AND playground.aggregate_service_map.storage_service_name = playground.storage_service_level.storage_service_name UNION SELECT DISTINCT playground.storage_service_level.storage_service_name, playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle AS 'iops_throttle', IF (playground.storage_service_level.thin_min is NULL, CAST( playground.qos_default_values.thin_min * playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle / 100 AS SIGNED), CAST(playground.storage_service_level.thin_min * playground.storage_service_level.iops_throttle / 100 AS SIGNED)) AS 'MinimimSLA', playground.storage_service_level.comment FROM playground.storage_service_level, playground.qos_default_values WHERE playground.storage_service_level.aggr_include_regex != "" ) AS sl WHERE '${UsingSLC}' = 'false'

user-input.description: Select the PSLC to be used for Volume Provisioning
user-input.name: $PSLName

user-input-type.query: SELECT Name, Comment FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT playground.protection_service_level.protection_service_name AS 'Name', playground.protection_service_level.comment AS 'Comment' FROM playground.protection_service_level UNION SELECT "None", "No protection" ) AS PSL WHERE '${UsingSLC}' = 'false'

user-input.description: The volume name can contain letters, numbers, and the underscore character (_), but the first character must be a letter or an underscore
user-input.name: $VolumeName

user-input.description: Provide size for the volume in GB.
user-input.name: $Size
